"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480670","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-23","<p>The Department for Transport’s current assessment is that none of its senior civil servants, including those in its agencies or other public bodies, will fall under the provisions of the fourth EU Money Laundering Directive, 2015/849.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-03-23T15:44:34.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480670/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480670/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480670/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-18","Money Laundering: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of its senior civil servants who will potentially fall under the provisions of the Fourth EU Money Laundering Directive, 2015/849; and what assessment he has made of which of his Department's agencies or other public bodies will potentially be classed as holding a prominent public function for the purposes of that directive.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","31719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480671","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-23","<p>As confirmed by my right honourable friend the Secretary of State in his statement to the House on 21 March, the proposed changes to PIP will not be going ahead.</p><p> </p><p>We spend around £50bn every year on benefits alone to support people with disabilities or health conditions, with spending on Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA) having increased by more than £3 billion since 2010. The government is committed to talking to disabled people, their representatives, healthcare professionals and employers to ensure the welfare system works better with the health and social care systems and provides help and support to those who need it most.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-03-23T11:13:17.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480671/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480671/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480671/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-18","Personal Independence Payment: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect on levels of poverty of the proposed reforms to personal independence payment in the Budget 2016.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","31737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480672","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-23","<p>Whilst there have been changes to Universal Credit since the impact assessment in 2012, these have not fundamentally altered the service, which remains on course to deliver stronger work incentives and simplicity in the welfare system.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-23T10:05:19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480672/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480672/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480672/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-18","Universal Credit: Impact Assessments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will conduct a revised impact assessment for universal credit on the effect of reforms to its design since 2012.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","31736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480673","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-30","<p>There is no requirement for Jobseekers Allowance claimants to undertake 35 hours of job search a week. Claimants must however be actively seeking work in each week of their claim. This means they are expected to do all that they reasonably can to give them the best prospects of securing employment.</p><p> </p><p>We recognise the benefits that volunteering can offer in enhancing a claimant’s prospects of finding suitable employment. Time spent volunteering may therefore be taken into account when considering whether a person has taken all appropriate steps to actively seek work each week.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-30T14:11:28.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480673/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480673/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/480673/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-18","Jobseeker's Allowance: Voluntary Work","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect on jobseeker's allowance claimants taking up volunteer work of the requirement for them to spend 35 hours each week searching for work; and whether that assessment was conducted prior to implementation of that policy.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","31780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479477","Attorney General","false","2016-03-23","<p>The Law Officers’ Departments have not received any such funding.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2016-03-23T10:35:29.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479477/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479477/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479477/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-03-17","Attorney General: European Social Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how much his Department received from the European Social Fund between 2007 and 2014; and how much his Department further received from the European Social Investment Fund from 2014 to the last month for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","31679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479478","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-31","<p>Running costs for 2014-15 for the 56 projects are given in Appendix 3 of the NAO Science Capital report where facilities are operational. These figures come from the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) and its Partner Organisations and provide an indication of annual running costs of these projects.</p><p>Project level management and allocation of funding for the majority of ongoing science projects is done at Partner Organisation level, in accordance with the delivery responsibilities of the Partner Organisations BIS funds. BIS does not hold this level of information centrally and it would not be possible to collect this information for each of the years since 2007, and estimates for future years, without disproportionate cost. However, the Government has protected the science and research budget in real terms in the 2015 spending review to ensure science spending remains on a sustainable footing and continues to deliver world-class research.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-31T14:52:05.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479478/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479478/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479478/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-17","Science: Capital Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the running costs were for the 56 capital based science projects which his Department has funded for each year since 2007, referred to in the NAO Report entitled BIS's capital investment in science projects, HC 885, published on 10 March 2016; and what the projected running costs for those projects are for each year to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","31687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479480","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-29","<p>The information requested is accessible via Tables LRW1and LRW2 of our 2005 and 2010 NDR Challenges and changes publications. Links below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479037/NDR_2010_Challenges_and_Changes.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479037/NDR_2010_Challenges_and_Changes.xls</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479045/NDR_2005_Challenges_and_Changes.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479045/NDR_2005_Challenges_and_Changes.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-03-29T10:34:14.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479480/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479480/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479480/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-17","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many non-domestic rate arrears appeals were (a) lodged and (b) heard in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","31686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479481","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-31","<p>The Student Loans Company does not hold information on the number of student loan applicants with discretionary leave to remain who have had their application for support refused.</p><p>A public consultation on the introduction of a new category of eligibility for those with long residence in the UK, including periods of discretionary leave, closed in January 2016. The consultation can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/student-support-for-non-UK-nationals-who-have-lived-in-the-UK-for-a-long-time" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/student-support-for-non-UK-nationals-who-have-lived-in-the-UK-for-a-long-time</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-31T14:53:16.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479481/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479481/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479481/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-17","Overseas Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people were refused student loans as a result of their discretionary leave to remain immigration status in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","31672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479482","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-11","<p>We have developed our methodology over time, starting in 2010 when there was no reliable estimate for spend with small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). We now have much better data than before 2010 and we are continuing to improve our understanding of spend. The Government exceeded its target of 25% of central government procurement spend going to small and medium businesses by 2015, achieving over £12 billion (27.1%) of spend with SMEs by the end of the last Parliament.</p><p>The Government standardised its methodology for collecting data on direct spend with SMEs in 2011-12; data on direct spend published since that point is comparable. Data on indirect spend for 2013-14 and 2014-15 is also comparable. This is an area of continuous improvement and we intend to standardise our methodology again during 2016-17.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-11T10:16:45.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479482/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479482/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479482/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-17","Government Departments: Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make it his policy to develop a standardised methodology for measuring SME spending by government departments which can be used as a baseline over the next five years.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","31682"
