"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479484","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-22","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>UK Trade &amp; Investment does not hold information on staff with direct experience of working in private sector exporting companies. I can however confirm that a large number of its staff have been recruited from the private sector.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-22T16:27:10.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479484/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479484/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479484/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-17","UK Trade and Investment: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many UK Trade and Industry (UKTI) staff have direct experience of working in private sector exporting companies before taking up their employment at UKTI.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","31661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479485","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-05","<p>The Intellectual Property Office (IPO) estimates that 5% of global graphene patent documents published between 2005 and 2014 have coverage in the UK (in that they are applications to the IPO or the European Patent Office (EPO) with effect in the UK, but were not necessarily filed by UK applicants).</p><p> </p><p>In the same period, UK applicants were responsible for filing 1% of published global graphene patent applications worldwide.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-04-05T10:43:10.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479485/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479485/answer","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479485/answer/previousversion/52914","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-17","Materials: Patents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the proportion of global patents for graphene that is held in the UK.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","31662"
