"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479590","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 10 March to PQ UIN 29688.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-03-22T15:19:01.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479590/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479590/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479590/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-03-17","Flood Control: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will take steps to facilitate an application from Lancaster City Council and the Environment Agency for funding for flood defences along the River Lune.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","31590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479591","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-22","<p>Defra officials have been investigating this issue since the meeting in November and are in the process of finalising the information mentioned above for the Sheep Dip Sufferers Group. This is expected to be completed and released shortly.</p><p> </p><p>The information will answer the actions from the meeting and include news releases from MAFF and the Veterinary Products Committee (VPC) from 1992 and 1993. These explain why the decision was taken to end compulsory dipping and the conclusions of the VPC reviews of organophosphate sheep dips at the time.</p><p> </p><p>A note of agreed actions from the meeting will be provided along with the information above.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-03-22T15:23:26.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479591/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479591/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479591/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-03-17","Sheep Dipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress her Department has made on the issues raised by the Sheep Dip Sufferers Support Group at the meeting of 19 November 2015 relating to (a) organophosphate sheep dip and (b) missing medical records from 1992; and if she will send the minutes of that meeting to the Sheep Dip Sufferers Support Group.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","31579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479592","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-24","<p>We are aware of reports that mass graves have been discovered in northern Iraq but our position on the matter has not changed. We continue to condemn in the strongest terms the targeting and persecution of Yazidis, Christians and other communities by Daesh. We continue to urge the Government of Iraq to do all it can to ensure the security and rights of all communities in Iraq. We are working to build consensus around the importance of freedom of religion or belief, including by funding practical projects designed to enhance community dialogue between civil society and faith groups.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-03-24T15:48:14.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479592/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479592/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479592/answer","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479592/answer/previousversion/52895","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Iraq: Genocide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 22 February 2016 to Question 26920, if he will offer the Iraqi government British forensic team support to investigate mass graves discovered in Sinjar.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","31582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479593","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Government is appalled by the brutal human rights abuses and violations of humanitarian law perpetrated by Daesh. There have been many credible reports of Daesh crimes, including public executions, torture, bodies routinely mutilated and put on public display, and mass executions. Any conviction of a person for Crimes Against Humanity, will be decided by a court after consideration of all the evidence available in the context of a credible judicial process.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-03-22T16:50:47.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479593/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479593/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479593/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Islamic State: Crimes against Humanity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment the Government has made of whether Daesh has been responsible for (a) crimes against humanity and (b) ethnic cleansing.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","31583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479595","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-24","The International Criminal Court Prosecutor set out some of the complicated issues involved in the ICC investigating Daesh in her statement of 8 April 2015. Under article 13 of the Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court, the Court may exercise its jurisdiction if a situation in a specified territory is referred to the Prosecutor by the UN Security Council. When efforts were made to refer the situation in Syria to the ICC in 2014, this proposed referral was vetoed by Russia and China. However, the Government remains committed to working with our international partners to ensure that Daesh is held to account for its crimes and that those who have suffered at its hand receive justice.","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-03-24T15:54:15.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479595/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479595/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479595/answer","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479595/answer/previousversion/52896","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Islamic State: Genocide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on the UN Security Council referring evidence of potential genocide by Daesh to the International Criminal Court.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","31584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479596","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-24","<p>The US Secretary of State is right to draw attention to the appalling crimes Daesh are committing, both against minorities groups and Muslims. We will continue to work closely with the US and our other partners in the Global Coalition to defeat Daesh and to ensure justice for those who have suffered at their hands. It is a long standing UK policy that any judgement on whether genocide has occurred should be a matter for judicial decision, rather than for governments. As Secretary of State Kerry said, “ultimately, the full facts must be brought to light by an independent investigation and through formal legal determination made by a competent court or tribunal.”</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-03-24T15:59:48.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479596/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479596/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479596/answer","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479596/answer/previousversion/52899","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Islamic State: Yazidis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 22 February 2016 to Question 26922 and the statement with reference to genocide on 17 March 2016 by the US Secretary of State on Daesh atrocities, if he will reassess the Government's policy on judgements as to whether genocide has occurred.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","31585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479597","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-22","<p>I frequently discuss Daesh with US Secretary of State Kerry, including their appalling brutality towards both Muslims and minorities, such as the Yazidis.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-03-22T16:38:27.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479597/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479597/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479597/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Islamic State: Yazidis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with US Secretary of State on the killing of Yazidis by Daesh.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","31586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479598","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-24","<p>Our Embassy in Tel Aviv has raised UK concerns with the Israeli Government on this issue. We continue to encourage the Israeli authorities and Bedouin communities to work together to identify a satisfactory solution. Any solution must respect the equality of all Israel’s citizens, and be consistent with Israel’s commitments under international law.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-24T15:44:35.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479598/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479598/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479598/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Israel: Bedouin","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Israeli counterparts on the demolition of the village of Umm el-Hiran.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","31592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479599","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-29","<p>The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) replied to the letter from the Hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton (Sir Gerald Kaufman) of 9 February with regard to Ms M Hamilton on 22 March.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-29T14:54:21.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479599/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479599/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479599/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he intends to answer the letter to him dated 9 February from the right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton with regard to Ms M Hamilton.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","31607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479600","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-29","<p>We continue to follow this case closely, raising it at ministerial and official level at every opportunity, as we have done since November 2013. Following the court ruling on 11 January 2016 Ministers have raised the case with Foreign Secretary Jaishankar, the Minister of State for External Affairs, Mr VK Singh and the Indian High Commissioner Mr Navtej Singh.</p><p>Whilst we cannot interfere in any foreign legal process, we shall continue to use every opportunity to raise the case at all levels, calling for any legal proceedings to move forward quickly.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-03-29T14:00:04.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479600/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479600/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479600/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","India: MV Seaman Guard Ohio","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to the Indian government on the Seaman Guard Ohio since the Indian court ruling relating to that matter in January 2016.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","31597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479602","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-22","<p>The British Embassy in Luanda has been in close contact with the Government of Angola and the World Health Organisation regarding the current outbreak of yellow fever. The UK is the largest donor to Gavi (the Vaccine Alliance) and is providing £1.44 billion for 2016-2020. Gavi is supporting Angola’s response through the International Coordination Group’s Revolving Fund. We understand that Angola has received 7 million doses from the International Coordination Group to respond to the outbreak. The UK is also supporting vaccinations for yellow fever in Luanda through the World Health Organisation.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-03-22T14:05:19.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479602/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479602/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479602/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Angola: Yellow Fever","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Angolan counterparts on the current outbreak of yellow fever in Angola.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","31562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479603","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-22","<p>We do not have figures on the number of people who reported torture in Bahrain however we unreservedly condemn torture and cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment or punishment. It is a priority for us to combat it wherever and whenever it occurs. We believe that UK support to Bahrain’s reform programme is the most constructive way to achieve long-lasting and sustainable reform in Bahrain. While it will take time to see the full results, UK support is having a direct, positive impact on areas of concern.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-22T16:51:36.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479603/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479603/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479603/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Bahrain: Torture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what estimate he has made of the number of people who have reported being tortured since the start of his Department's technical assistance programme in Bahrain.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","31696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479604","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-22","<p>We have raised Zainab Al Khawaja’s case with the Government of Bahrain at the highest levels. The UK encourages Bahrain to respect the rights of all peaceful opposition figures. We call on the Bahraini government to act proportionately in all such cases to protect the universal rights of freedom of expression and assembly. I most recently raised human rights with the Bahraini Ambassador to the UK, His Excellency Sheikh Fawaz bin Mohammed Al Khalifa , on 8 March.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-22T16:54:40.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479604/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479604/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479604/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Bahrain: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to the government of Bahrain on the imprisonment of Zainab Al Khawaja; and whether he plans to make representations to press for Zainab Al Khawaja's release.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","31697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479605","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-04-20","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office did not receive any funding from the European Social Fund in either period.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-04-20T13:35:27.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479605/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479605/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479605/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-17","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: European Social Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much funding his Department received from the European Social Fund (a) between 2007 and 2014 and (b) from 2014 to the last month for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","31641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479606","Department of Health","false","2016-03-24","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department has not directly received any funding from the European Social Fund during the period stated.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-03-24T14:46:07.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479606/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479606/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479606/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Department of Health: European Social Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much funding his Department received from the European Social Fund (a) between 2007 and 2014 and (b) from 2014 to the last month for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","31642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479607","Department of Health","false","2016-03-29","<p>The Department assesses the impact of tobacco control measures on an ongoing basis as it develops policy. The Smoke-Free (Private Vehicles) Regulations 2015 include a requirement to review the regulations within five years of them coming into force, which will include an assessment of the effect on children’s exposure to secondhand smoke in private vehicles.</p><p>In changing the law we always said the measure of success would be in changes in attitude and behaviour, not the number of enforcement actions. Information on prosecutions for the period since the regulations were introduced has not yet been published, however we would expect very few fixed penalty notices issued for these offences would lead to court appearances.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","31571","2016-03-29T10:00:25.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479607/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479607/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479607/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Motor Vehicles: Smoking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will commission an independent assessment of the effect on children of legislation on smoking in cars.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","31605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479608","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Government has been clear that there will be no saving to the public purse as a result of these changes. We are committing up to an additional £125 million to provide support to those affected by this tragedy over the course of this spending review period.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-03-22T16:35:33.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479608/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479608/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479608/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate the Government has made of the likely savings to the public purse of implementing the changes to financial support for people affected by HIV or hepatitis C through treatment with NHS-supplied blood or blood products set out in the Government's consultation.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479609","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>Since 1988 the Government has voluntarily provided ex gratia support for people affected by HIV and/or hepatitis C through treatment with NHS-supplied blood or blood products. To date, over £390 million has been paid out through the schemes, in the United Kingdom.</p><p>The Department only holds finance data for payments under the schemes back to 2007. This information is provided below.</p><p>2014-15 £22,278,096</p><p>2013-14 £27,043,569</p><p>2012-13 £22,052,458</p><p>2011-12 £27,192,232</p><p>2010-11 £39,805,667</p><p>2009-10 £22,461,057</p><p>2008-09 £19,240,337</p><p>2007-08 £20,532,461</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-03-22T11:47:14.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479609/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479609/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479609/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much financial support his Department has given to people affected by HIV or hepatitis C through treatment with NHS-supplied blood or blood products in each year since 1988.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479610","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>We have made no such estimates.</p><p>Herbal cannabis is not licensed as a medicine and, under section 7(4) of the Misuse of Drugs Act 1971, a pharmacist would need to obtain a licence from the Home Office if they were to dispense cannabis.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","31656 ; 31657","2016-03-22T16:47:04.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479610/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479610/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479610/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Cannabis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people using cannabis in the UK for medicinal purposes; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","31606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479612","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Department’s assessment is that Crown immunity does not limit an individual’s right to redress via legal action. Crown immunity does not protect from civil suit, but only from criminal prosecution. Indeed, some affected persons did bring an action in 1988, which was settled out of court, without establishment of liability.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-03-22T11:53:36.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479612/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479612/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479612/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of Crown immunity on the ability to bring legal action on liability for the infection of patients with contaminated NHS blood.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","31621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479613","Department of Health","false","2016-03-23","<p>Information is not collected centrally on the number of prescriptions issued. However, information is available on the number of prescription items dispensed for Sativex in England between 2010 and 2014<sup>1</sup>.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Sativex prescription items written in the United Kingdom and dispensed in the community in England</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Prescription items (000s)</p></td><td><p>Net ingredient cost (£000s) <sup>2</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2.5</p></td><td><p>841.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>3.0</p></td><td><p>1,185.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2.8</p></td><td><p>1,141.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2.8</p></td><td><p>1,158.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2.7</p></td><td><p>1,148.3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> Prescription Cost Analysis system data provided by the Health and Social Care Information Centre</p><p><em>Notes: </em></p><p><sup>1 </sup>2015 full year data will be published by the Health and Social Care Information Centre on 7 April 2016 and will be available using the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/pubs/prescostanalysiseng2015" target="_blank">http://www.hscic.gov.uk/pubs/prescostanalysiseng2015</a></p><p> </p><p><sup>2 </sup>Net ingredient cost is the basic cost of a drug. It does not take account of discounts, dispensing costs, fees or prescription charges income.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-03-23T15:23:27.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479613/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479613/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479613/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-17","Nabiximols","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much prescriptions for Sativex were issued in each of the last five years.","true","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","31655"
