"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479128","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-23","Public libraries are funded and run by local authorities. My Department has through Arts Council England’s Library Development Funding, which supports the development of public libraries in England including workforce training, provided £680,000 in 2012/13; £683,000 in 2013/14; £595,000 in 2014/15; and £744,000 in 2015/16. Workforce development is also one of the priorities of the Leadership for Libraries Taskforce, established in 2015 by my Department and the Local Government Association.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","31476 ; 31482","2016-03-23T10:55:29.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479128/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479128/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/479128/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-16","Public Libraries: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what his Department's planned expenditure on workforce training for staff in public libraries was in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13, (d) 2013-14, (e) 2014-15 and (f) 2015-16 to date.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","31479"
